com.joliciel.talismane.posTagger

Interface PosTagger

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    NonDeterministicPosTagger

    public interface PosTagger
    The PosTagger's task is to add part-of-speech tags to words within a sentence. More specifically, the tagSentence(TokenSequence) method takes a TokenSequence as input and produces a PosTagSequence, which extends a List of PosTaggedToken.
    Author:
    Assaf Urieli

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static String POS_TAG_ATTRIBUTE
      If this attribute is added to a Token via Token.addAttribute(String, String) (typically using a TokenRegexFilter), the token in question will get the pos-tag in the attribute value assigned to it without consulting the statistical model.

    • Field Detail

      • POS_TAG_ATTRIBUTE

        static final String POS_TAG_ATTRIBUTE
        If this attribute is added to a Token via Token.addAttribute(String, String) (typically using a TokenRegexFilter), the token in question will get the pos-tag in the attribute value assigned to it without consulting the statistical model. This is an alternative to using pos-tagger rules.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        PosTagSequence tagSentence(TokenSequence tokenSequence)
        Apply PosTags to the tokens in a given sentence.

        Returns:
        a List of TaggedToken reflecting the PosTags applied to the tokens.
